works.description:
We’ve earlier brought you news of old  
airplanes being transformed into hotels and homes, and this time, we have  
an airplane turned into an restaurant. Enter Runway 34, a vintage  
airplane-turned-restaurant and bar in Zürich, Switzerland. This eatery was  
once a Soviet Ilyushin IL-14 airplane, which made its final flight in 2005.  
Located adjacent to Zurich International Airport, the Runway 34  
restaurant/bar has been refurbished with window-filled walls, wooden  
flooring and amazing mood lighting.
